'''Stjepan Radeljić''' ({{IPA|hr|stjêpan rǎdeʎitɕ|pron}}; born 5 September 1997) is a Bosnian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[Croatian Football League]] club [[HNK Rijeka|Rijeka]] and the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Radeljić started his professional career at [[VfB Stuttgart II]], before joining [[NK Osijek|Osijek]] in 2018, who loaned him to [[NK Široki Brijeg|Široki Brijeg]] in 2020 and to [[FC Sheriff Tiraspol|Sheriff Tiraspol]] in 2021, with whom he signed permanently a year later. The following year, he moved to Rijeka.

A former youth international for Bosnia and Herzegovina, Radeljić made his senior international debut in 2024.

==Club career==

===Early career===
Radeljić started playing football at [[NK Vitez|Vitez]], before joining [[HŠK Zrinjski Mostar|Zrinjski Mostar's youth academy]] in 2014. In July 2016, he signed with German team [[VfB Stuttgart]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/zvanicno-stjepan-radeljic-potpisao-za-stuttgart/160713053|title=Zvanično: Stjepan Radeljić potpisao za Stuttgart|website=klix.ba|date=13 July 2016|accessdate=14 July 2016|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

In June 2018, he moved to Croatian side [[NK Osijek|Osijek]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/253032-stjepan-radeljic-novi-igrac-osijeka|title=Stjepan Radeljić novi igrač Osijeka|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=10 June 2018|accessdate=12 June 2018|language=Bosnian}}</ref> He made his professional debut in a [[2018–19 UEFA Europa League#First qualifying round|UEFA Europa League qualifier]] against [[FC Petrocub Hîncești|Petrocub]] on 12 July at the age of 20.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://index.hr/sport/clanak/petrocub-osijek-11-maric-zabio-prvi-gol-u-novoj-sezoni-osijek-ispustio-pobjedu/2010776.aspx|title=Petrocub - Osijek 1:1 Marić zabio prvi gol u novoj sezoni, Osijek ispustio pobjedu |website=index.hr|date=12 July 2018|accessdate=12 July 2018|language=Croatian}}</ref> In January 2020, he was sent on a six-month loan to [[NK Široki Brijeg|Široki Brijeg]]. In July, his loan was extended for an additional season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/siroki-brijeg-i-osijek-dogovorili-novu-posudbu/367504|title=Široki Brijeg i Osijek dogovorili novu posudbu|website=sportsport.ba|date=4 July 2020|accessdate=6 July 2020|language=Bosnian}}</ref> On 29 February, he scored his first professional goal in a triumph over [[FK Mladost Doboj Kakanj|Mladost Doboj Kakanj]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/mladost-i-siroki-odigrali-sjajan-mec-gosti-u-nadoknadi-postigli-gol-za-bitna-tri-boda/353391|title=Mladost i Široki odigrali sjajan meč, gosti u nadoknadi postigli gol za bitna tri boda|website=sportsport.ba|date=29 February 2020|accessdate=1 March 2020|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

In February 2021, Radeljić was sent on a year-long loan to Moldovan outfit [[FC Sheriff Tiraspol|Sheriff Tiraspol]], with an option to make the transfer permanent, which was activated in January 2022.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://scsport.ba/nece-se-vracati-u-osijek-sheriff-tiraspol-otkupio-ugovor-bh-stopera|title=Neće se vraćati u Osijek: Sheriff Tiraspol otkupio ugovor bh. stopera|website=scsport.ba|date=2 January 2022|accessdate=2 January 2022|language=Bosnian}}</ref> He debuted in the [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League#Group D|UEFA Champions League]] against [[FC Shakhtar Donetsk|Shakhtar Donetsk]] on 15 September.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/pjaniceva-asistencija-nedovoljna-besiktasu-pobjeda-sheriffa-na-debiju-u-ligi-prvaka/101105|title=Pjanićeva asistencija nedovoljna Beşiktaşu, pobjeda Sheriffa na debiju u Ligi prvaka|website=faktor.ba|date=15 September 2021|accessdate=18 September 2021|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

===Rijeka===
In July 2023, Radeljić signed a three-year deal with [[HNK Rijeka|Rijeka]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/395403-jakirovic-u-rijeku-doveo-bivseg-u21-reprezentativca-bih|title=Jakirović u Rijeku doveo bivšeg U21 reprezentativca BiH|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=13 July 2023|accessdate=14 July 2023|language=Bosnian}}</ref> He made his official debut for the squad in a [[2023–24 UEFA Europa Conference League#Second qualifying round|UEFA Europa Conference League qualifier]] against [[KF Dukagjini|Dukagjini]] on 27 July.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://index.hr/sport/clanak/dukagjini-rijeka-0-1-jankovic-sjajnim-golom-donio-rijeci-pobjedu-na-kosovu/2483020.aspx|title=Dukagjini - Rijeka 0:1 Janković sjajnim golom donio Rijeci pobjedu na Kosovu|website=index.hr|date=27 July 2023|accessdate=30 July 2023|language=Croatian}}</ref> On 10 August, he scored his first goal for Rijeka in a [[2023–24 UEFA Europa Conference League#Third qualifying round|UEFA Europa Conference League qualifier]] against [[B36 Tórshavn]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://index.hr/sport/clanak/torshavn-rijeka-13-rijeka-preokretom-na-farskim-otocima-na-korak-do-playoffa/2486510.aspx|title=Tórshavn - Rijeka 1:3 Rijeka preokretom na Farskim otocima na korak do play-offa|website=index.hr|date=10 August 2023|accessdate=12 August 2023|language=Croatian}}</ref> Two weeks later, he made his league debut against [[NK Lokomotiva|Lokomotiva]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://index.hr/sport/clanak/rijeka-lokomotiva-21-rijeka-preokretom-do-pete-uzastopne-pobjede-u-sezoni/2488106.aspx|title=Rijeka - Lokomotiva 2:1 Rijeka preokretom do pete uzastopne pobjede u sezoni|website=index.hr|date=20 August 2023|accessdate=22 August 2023|language=Croatian}}</ref> On 25 August 2024, he scored his first league goal in a defeat of Osijek.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://index.hr/sport/clanak/sjajni-pasalic-donio-rijeci-veliku-pobjedu-osijek-ostao-na-dnu-shnla/2592798.aspx|title=Sjajni Pašalić donio Rijeci veliku pobjedu, Osijek ostao na dnu SHNL-a|website=index.hr|date=25 August 2024|accessdate=26 August 2024|language=Croatian}}</ref> He won his first trophy with the club on 25 May 2025, when they were crowned league champions.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/rijeka-u-ludom-raspletu-sezone-postala-prvak-hrvatske-ispred-dinama-i-hajduka/250525090|title=Rijeka u ludom raspletu sezone postala prvak Hrvatske ispred Dinama i Hajduka|website=klix.ba|date=25 May 2025|accessdate=28 May 2025|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

==International career==
Radeljić represented [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] at various youth levels.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/reprezentacija/radeljic-reprezentativni-poziv-je-slag-na-tortu-ove-vrlo-dobre-sezone-958197|title=Radeljić: Reprezentativni poziv je šlag na tortu ove vrlo dobre sezone|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=30 May 2024|accessdate=1 June 2024|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

In May 2024, he received his first senior call up, for [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] games against [[England national football team|England]] and [[Italy national football team|Italy]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/ovo-je-barbarezov-spisak-za-englesku-i-italiju-pozvano-sedam-novih-zmajeva/545686|title=Ovo je Barbarezov spisak za Englesku i Italiju: Pozvano sedam novih Zmajeva|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=16 May 2024|accessdate=18 May 2024|language=Bosnian}}</ref> He debuted against the former on 3 June.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/engleska-slavila-protiv-bih-zmajevi-u-barbarezovom-debiju-za-pola-sata-potopljeni-u-newcastleu/189628|title=Engleska slavila protiv BiH: Zmajevi u Barbarezovom debiju za pola sata potopljeni u Newcastleu|website=faktor.ba|date=3 June 2024|accessdate=4 June 2024|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

